{
  "text": "\u2022 Limited applicability signature-wise. As a rule, most of the proposed methods work well only if the corresponding signature contains some minimum number of high p T isolated leptons. Leptonic signatures have the twofold advantage of lower SM backgrounds and good lepton momentum measurement. The performance of the methods typically deteriorates as we lower the number of leptons in the signature. The most challenging [CITATION_1] See Ref. [CITATION_2] for a recent review. [CITATION_3] Worse still, there are even fewer ideas for measuring the spins of the new particles in a truly modelindependent fashion [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6538701",
